Game Design Document (GDD)
Title: ATLAS HIVE: Surface Extraction
Genre: Co-op Multiplayer Zombie Extraction Shooter / Survival
Perspective: First-person
Target Platforms: PC (primary), Consoles
Target Audience: Fans of Escape from Tarkov, Deep Rock Galactic, Left 4 Dead, and The Division
Development Stage: Concept

1. High Concept
A tense, co-op multiplayer extraction shooter where teams of survivors depart from underground hive bunkers via maglev trains to scavenge the ruined surface world. The goal is to recover critical electrical components, pre-collapse technology, and scientific knowledge to keep the last human hives operational. Every run is high-risk: limited time on the surface, evolving zombie threats, and permanent consequences for failure.
Core Fantasy: You are the lifeline for underground civilization — part soldier, part scavenger, part scientist — venturing into a post-apocalyptic world ruined by an English-engineered bioweapon.

2. Story & Setting
Backstory
In 2028, a rogue British bioweapons program released a engineered pathogen (codename: “Erebus”). It spread globally within months. The first 24 hours featured full aerosol transmission. After the initial airborne phase, the virus mutated and stabilized — it now only transmits through blood and saliva (bites, scratches, open wounds mixed with infected fluids).
Nations collapsed. The few remaining survivors retreated into pre-built and hastily expanded underground bunker networks called Hives. These self-sustaining arcologies rely on geothermal power, hydroponics, and aging pre-war technology. Resources are running out.
Atlas Corporation is one of the largest remaining factions operating multiple Hives. Players belong to Atlas Corp and take on the role of Field Operators — elite soldiers, medics, engineers, and scientists.
Tone: Grounded, gritty, and claustrophobic. Hope mixed with desperation. Scientific realism where possible.

3. Core Gameplay Loop
	1.  Mission Briefing – Choose a surface location via the Hive command interface.
	2.  Deployment – Load into an underground maglev train that takes the squad to the chosen egress point.
	3.  Surface Run – Explore, scavenge, complete objectives, and survive.
	4.  Extraction – Reach an extraction point (or call one) before the timer expires or horde density becomes overwhelming. Return to the Hive with loot.
	5.  Hive Phase – Turn in components and data for Hive upgrades, personal progression, and better gear for future runs.
Run Duration: 45–90 minutes (player-selectable difficulty affects timer and rewards).

4. Key Features
Transmission & Infection Mechanics
•  No airborne transmission anymore (safe to breathe).
•  Infection only occurs via direct fluid contact (bites, blood splatter in open wounds, etc.).
•  Players have a visible infection timer + diagnostic HUD.
•  Field medics can administer antivirals to slow or reset early-stage infection.
•  Late-stage infection = player turns and must be put down (permadeath risk on high difficulties).
Scavenging & Objectives
•  Primary goal: Recover electrical/high-tech components (transformers, capacitors, server blades, quantum drives, research data cores, solar arrays, etc.).
•  Secondary objectives: Collect scientific knowledge (hard drives, lab notes, prototype tech), medical supplies, rare materials.
•  Dynamic points of interest: abandoned data centers, universities, power substations, military bases, hospitals, factories.
Extraction System
•  Players must physically carry heavy loot (inventory weight/encumbrance system).
•  Extraction trains or choppers can be called but attract massive hordes.
•  Failed extractions = lost loot and possible permanent loss of operator.

5. Multiplayer
•  1–4 players recommended (up to 6 on larger maps).
•  Drop-in / Drop-out support.
•  Friendly fire always on.
•  Voice proximity and radio comms.
•  Class synergy strongly encouraged.

Playable Roles / Classes (can be mixed):
•  Combat Specialist – Heavy firepower, breaching, tanking.
•  Field Medic / Virologist – Healing, infection management, analysis.
•  Engineer / Technician – Drone support, hacking, faster looting, trap deployment.
•  Scout / Infiltrator – Stealth, mapping, light gear for faster movement.

6. Progression & Hive Economy
•  Hive Level – Collective progress. Successfully extracted components permanently upgrade the bunker (better gear unlocks, longer safe surface time, new train destinations, etc.).
•  Personal Progression – Operator rank, skills, loadout customization.
•  Risk/Reward – Higher difficulty locations = better loot and bigger Hive contributions.
•  Permadeath option available for hardcore servers.

7. Enemies & Threats
•  Standard Infected – Slow but numerous. Classic shamblers.
•  Runners – Fast, aggressive (early-infection victims).
•  Spitters / Bloated – Ranged acid or area denial.
•  Smart Infected (“Reclaimers”) – Later-game variants that use basic tools, set ambushes, remember player locations.
•  Environmental threats: Collapsing buildings, radiation pockets, rival scavenger factions, automated defense systems.
Horde Escalation – The longer a team stays, the more noise they make, the larger and smarter the hordes become.

8. Art & Audio Direction
•  Realistic dark post-apocalyptic visuals with overgrown English/European + American ruins.
•  Dynamic weather and day/night cycle (night runs are extremely dangerous).
•  Tense, industrial soundtrack mixed with distant moans and radio static.

9. Monetization
•  Cosmetic operator skins, weapon skins, Hive decoration.
•  Battle pass with cosmetic rewards.
•  No pay-to-win.